Introduction
------------
MishiGame is a tetris-like game. It runs on all systems on that SDL libraries
and C compiler was ported (Linux, *BSD, MacOS, Win32, BeOS, ...), but it was
tested only on Linux and Win32. You may have problems with running on other
platforms.


Requirements
------------
 * C compiler, linker
 * ANSI C header files
 * SDL libraries and header files (libSDL and libSDL_image)


Contacts
--------
homepage:              http://mishigame.sourceforge.net
e-mail address:        sebek64@post.cz

SDL Homepage:          http://www.libsdl.org


Game controls
-------------
	[ESC]		Stop current game, exit

	[F2]		New game

	[F3]		Continue paused game

	[F4]		Pause game

	[F5]		Print best scores

	[F6]		Decrease game speed

	[F7]		Increase game speed

	[<-]		Move left

	[->]		Move right

	[\/]		Move down

	[space]		Rotate


Command line arguments
----------------------
	--help		Prints command line arguments

	--version	Prints version number

	--copy		Prints copyright notice

	--fullscreen	Use fullscreen mode

	--speed	val	Sets game speed
